Rescue efforts are continuing for three miners trapped by a rockfall at Harmony Gold's Kusasalethu operations near Carletonville on Friday. JOHANNESBURG - Rescue efforts are continuing for three miners trapped by a rockfall at Harmony Gold's Kusasalethu operations near Carletonville on Friday. The bodies of two workers were brought to the surface over the weekend. The five became trapped underground following a tremor. Harmony Gold spokesperson Lauren Fourie says: Our condolences go out to their friends and family. We will not rest until we find the other three miners. (Edited by Shimoney Regter)